<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="362" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1099,2026]" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1099,1125]" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[542,721,1099,1125]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Distoleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tappa">
<emphasis box="[542,721,1099,1125]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Distoleon tappa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the distinct lateral yellow stripes on thorax (
<figureCitation box="[238,379,1135,1161]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,747,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-285@14.[151,1436,741,1913]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Thorax, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418734/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Figs 13A, C</figureCitation>
), absence of the black stripe below antennal toruli (
<figureCitation box="[960,1062,1135,1161]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,747,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-285@14.[151,1436,741,1913]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Thorax, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418734/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
), and the narrow cubital marking on forewing (
<figureCitation box="[304,376,1171,1197]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1934,1958]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,249,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-41@10.[151,1436,237,1911]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distoleon tappa Walker. A. Male right wing; B. Female right wing. Scale bar: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418726/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Figs 9</figureCitation>
A–B). Moreover, the male sternum 9 is nearly quadrate in ventral view, with a deep V-shaped incision on the posterior median margin (
<figureCitation box="[613,715,1207,1234]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1998,2022]" captionTargetBox="[163,1431,1451,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-42@16.[151,1435,1448,1974]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 16. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Male genitalia, lateral view, B. Same, ventral view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418740/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Fig. 16B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1099,2026]" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,363,1243,1269]" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Measurement</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount box="[383,404,1243,1269]" pageId="13" pageNumber="360" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
n=4; unit mm). Forewing length 32.0–34.5, width 9.5–10.0; hind wing length 31.5–33.8, width 7.7–8.0; body length 29.5–31.5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1099,2026]" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1315,1341]" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Re-description.</emphasis>
Head. Face yellow, without black stripe below base of antennal toruli; interantennal marking distinct, shiny black without setae; frons yellow, covered with short yellow setae (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1200,1351,1377]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,747,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-285@14.[151,1436,741,1913]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Thorax, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418734/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). Vertex raised, dark brown, with a narrow median longitudinal yellow stripe above black mark of antennae, dorsal part heavily marked with yellowish brown and brownish spots, covered with short brown setae; occiput with crown-shaped yellow marking (
<figureCitation box="[262,367,1459,1485]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,747,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-285@14.[151,1436,741,1913]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Thorax, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418734/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
). Antennae longer than length of head and prothorax combined; clavate; toruli yellow; scape and pedicel yellow but brownish at base; flagellomeres annulated with brown and pinkish rings, covered with short black setae (
<figureCitation box="[288,392,1531,1557]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,747,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-285@14.[151,1436,741,1913]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Thorax, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418734/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Figs 13B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[404,454,1531,1558]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1400,1424]" captionTargetBox="[180,1403,185,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-19@16.[171,1415,181,1376]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 15. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Right hind leg; B. Right foreleg; C. Antenna. Scale bar: 0.5 mm (A, B)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418738" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418738/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">15C</figureCitation>
). Maxillary and labial palps, labrum, clypeus, gena and face yellow; labrum with brown, erect setae; clypeus with yellowish brown and black setae. Labial palpi with distal palpomere spindle-shaped with an acute apex, palpimacula brownish, small and circular, narrowed basally (
<figureCitation box="[1000,1105,1603,1629]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,747,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-285@14.[151,1436,741,1913]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Thorax, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418734/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Figs 13B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1117,1154,1603,1630]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[257,1330,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[257,1330,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lateral view of Distoleon species. A. D. sambalpurensis; B. D. tappa; C. D. verendus. Scale bar: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418718/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1099,2026]" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
Thorax. Brownish black (
<figureCitation box="[488,593,1639,1665]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[165,1425,747,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-285@14.[151,1436,741,1913]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Thorax, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418734/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum narrow, as long as or slightly broader than long, with a narrow median and broadly lateral yellow stripes; lateral and posterior margins brownish black; pronotum wholly covered with short black setae; anterolateral corner with short white setae, lateral margins with long black and white setae, posterior margin with long black setae. Mesonotum brownish black, with a narrow median and slightly broader lateral yellow stripes; posterolateral margins of mesoscutum yellowish brown with long white setae, anterolateral margins slightly yellowish brown with two district yellowish spots near at wing base; lateral and posterior margins of mesoscutum yellowish brown with long white setae. Metanotum dark brown with a narrow median and slightly broader lateral yellow strips; posterior margin of metascutellum covered with long white setae. Thoracic pleurites dark brown, covered with long white setae (
<figureCitation box="[643,732,1927,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[257,1330,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[257,1330,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lateral view of Distoleon species. A. D. sambalpurensis; B. D. tappa; C. D. verendus. Scale bar: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418718/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1099,2026]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1437,151,717]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="361" pageId="13" pageNumber="360">
Legs. Foreleg. Coxa yellow, brownish black ventrally with a narrow yellow stripe, covered with yellow setae. Trochanter yellow. Femur yellow, posterodorsally dark brown, covered mostly with short, white setae and a few long, black setae, femoral sense hair longer than fore femora. Tibia yellow with dispersed black dots at setal bases, dorsally with three black rings, covered with black setae, tibial spurs curved, as long as tarsomeres 1–4. Tarsomeres yellow, tarsomeres 1–3 brownish apically, last tarsal segment as long as tarsomeres 1–4, black apically. Middle leg. Coxa yellow, brownish at base, covered with long yellow setae. Trochanter yellowish. Femora yellow with mixed black and white setae, femoral sense hair longer than fore femora. Tibia yellow with black dots at setal bases, dorsally with three black rings, covered with black setae, tibial spurs curved, as long as tarsomeres 1–4. Hind leg. Coxa yellow, brownish at base, covered with long yellow setae. Trochanter yellowish. Femur yellow, posterodorsally dark brown, mixed with black and white setae. Tibia yellow, with black circular dots ventrally, covered with black setae, tibial spurs curved, as long as tarsomeres 1–3 (
<figureCitation box="[675,764,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[257,1330,183,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[257,1330,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lateral view of Distoleon species. A. D. sambalpurensis; B. D. tappa; C. D. verendus. Scale bar: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418718/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="361">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="361">
Wings. Relatively broad, subacute at apex (
<figureCitation box="[690,774,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1150,1174]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,188,1119]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[151,1436,181,1126]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 14. Distoleon verendus Walker. Right fore- and hind wing. Scale bar: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418736" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418736/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="361">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), membrane hyaline, longitudinal veins with alternate sections of black with many yellow stripes, bearing short black sparse setae; distal part and posterior margin of both wings with forked veins, base of each fork in forewing brownish. Forewing with seven presectoral crossveins; Rs diverged from R beyond cubital fork; Rs with 13 branches; pterostigma pinkish; cubital mark narrowly dark brown. Hind wing with one presectoral crossvein; Rs diverged from R beyond cubital fork; Rs with 12 branches; pterostigma pinkish, hardly visible; cubital mark indistinct; distal part of hind wing in female with an oblong brown marking at marginal fork of MP1 (
<figureCitation box="[538,622,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[313,1273,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[313,1273,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 17. Dorsal habitus of Walker’s species of Myrmeleon (Distoleon) from India and Nepal. A. Myrmeleon tappa Walker (Distoleon tappa), syntype, male; B. Myrmeleon verendus Walker (Distoleon verendus), holotype, female; C. Myrmeleon vesanus Walker (Distoleon verendus), holotype, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418742/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="361">Figs 17</figureCitation>
B–C).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418734" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4418734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418734/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="361" startId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" targetBox="[165,1425,747,1904]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1937,1997]" pageId="14" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1937,1961]" pageId="14" pageNumber="361">FIGURE 13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Walker. A." authorityName="Walker. A." box="[295,606,1937,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Distoleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verendus">
<emphasis box="[295,491,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="361">Distoleon verendus</emphasis>
Walker. A.
</taxonomicName>
Thorax, dorsal view; B. Face; C. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm (A); 0.5 mm (B, C).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418736" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4418736" box="[151,1046,1150,1174]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418736/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="362" startId="15.[151,250,1150,1174]" targetBox="[157,1427,188,1119]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1046,1150,1174]" box="[151,1046,1150,1174]" pageId="15" pageNumber="362">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1150,1174]" pageId="15" pageNumber="362">FIGURE 14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Walker. Right" authorityName="Walker. Right" box="[294,635,1150,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Myrmeleontidae" genus="Distoleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="362" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verendus">
<emphasis box="[294,489,1150,1174]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="362">Distoleon verendus</emphasis>
Walker. Right
</taxonomicName>
fore- and hind wing. Scale bar: 2.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1220,2039]" pageId="15" pageNumber="362">
Abdomen. Pale brown, covered with short black and white setae. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1203,1220,1247]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1998,2022]" captionTargetBox="[163,1431,1451,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-42@16.[151,1435,1448,1974]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 16. Distoleon verendus Walker. A. Male genitalia, lateral view, B. Same, ventral view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418740" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418740/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="362">Figs 16</figureCitation>
A–B): Tergum 9 and sternum 9 separated; tergum 9 nearly quadrate, covered with black and white setae; sternum 9 nearly quadrate in ventral view, anterior- and posterior margins slightly narrow, posterior margin medially with a deep V-shaped incision covered with long black setae; ectoproct oval, ventrolaterally elongated, covered with black setae becoming much longer ventrally, white setae along lateral margins.
</paragraph>
